block.p: Mary Jean Fell and Lt. Jeffrey Christopher Casler were married yesterday by the Rev. Frank McNulty, who officiated at the wedding of the bride's parents 40 years ago. The ceremony took place at the Roman Catholic Church of St. Thomas More in New York.

The bride is an associate at Blumenfeld & Cohen, a Washington law firm. She graduated from the College of the Holy Cross and received a law degree cum laude from Catholic University in Washington. She is a daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Laurence T. Fell of New York. Her father is a managing director for institutional accounts at M. J. Whitman, an investment firm in New York. Her mother, Eileen S. Fell, is a member of the board of the auxiliary of St. Vincents Hospital and Medical Center in New York and of the College of St. Elizabeth in Convent Station, N.J.

Mary Jean Fell and Lt. Jeffrey Christopher Casler were married yesterday by the Rev. Frank McNulty, who officiated at the wedding of the bride's parents 40 years ago. The ceremony took place at the Roman Catholic Church of St. Thomas More in New York.

The bride is an associate at Blumenfeld & Cohen, a Washington law firm. She graduated from the College of the Holy Cross and received a law degree cum laude from Catholic University in Washington. She is a daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Laurence T. Fell of New York. Her father is a managing director for institutional accounts at M. J. Whitman, an investment firm in New York. Her mother, Eileen S. Fell, is a member of the board of the auxiliary of St. Vincents Hospital and Medical Center in New York and of the College of St. Elizabeth in Convent Station, N.J.

The bridegroom is a judge advocate in the Navy and an instructor at the Naval Justice School in Newport, R.I. Lieutenant Casler graduated magna cum laude from the University of Scranton and received a law degree from George Washington University. He is a son of Mr. and Mrs. Richard E. Casler of Lyndhurst, N.J. His father retired as a production manager in Hoboken, N.J., for Kraft General Foods. The bridegroom's mother, Marie E. Casler, manages a physician's office in Kearny, N.J.
